external_knowledge:
- "Top-performing ads" are those that have the highest number of clicks within their respective campaigns.;
- "Click-through rate (CTR)" is calculated as the number of clicks divided by the number of impressions.;
- "Conversion tracking" is a feature that tracks specific actions taken by users after clicking on an ad.;
- "Average performance metrics" are calculated by averaging the clicks, impressions, and spend across all ads.

- 'Fruitful ad groups' refers to those with the highest average conversion values;
- 'Richness of their average conversion value' means the highest average conversion value;
- 'Top 3 ranked ad groups' refers to the ad groups with the highest average conversion values within each campaign.

- "Captured the most attention" refers to the ads with the highest number of clicks;
- "Reaped the greatest rewards" refers to the campaigns with the highest conversion value;
- Performance metrics include clicks, impressions, spend, conversion count, conversion value, cost per conversion, and click-through rate.

- "attracted the most attention" refers to campaigns with the highest number of clicks;
- "total attention they garnered" refers to the total number of clicks received by the campaign;
- "total investment made" refers to the total amount spent on the campaign;
- "average effectiveness of their ads" refers to the average click-through rate (CTR) of the ads within the campaign.

- "blossoming premium campaigns" refers to active campaigns in premium accounts;
- "drawing bees (keywords)" means using active keywords;
- "spending more than the average nectar (5.0 units of spend)" means the average spend on the ad is greater than 5.0.

- 'Higher-than-average' implies the value is greater than the mean of the respective metric across all accounts;
- 'Total ad spend' is the sum of the amount spent on all ads by an account;
- 'Average performance score' is the mean performance score of all keywords associated with the ads of an account.

